HEADWORD: Clownishness
<hw>Clown"ish*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The manners of a clown;
coarseness or rudeness of behavior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That plainness which the alamode people call
<qex>clownishness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cloy</ent>⟦br⟧
